2.2 Code Style Rules

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT: Use TypeScript when possible
interface UserData {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  email: string;
}

// ✅ CORRECT: Use const for non-reassignable variables
const API_URL = process.env.API_URL;

// ✅ CORRECT: Use descriptive variable names
const isVideoGenerationComplete = true;  // Good
const x = true;                           // Bad - not descriptive

// ✅ CORRECT: Handle errors properly
try {
  await generateVideo(options);
} catch (error) {
  logger.error('Video generation failed', { error });
  throw new AppError(500, 'Failed to generate video');
}

// ❌ INCORRECT: Swallow errors
try {
  await generateVideo(options);
} catch (error) {
  console.log('error');  // Not descriptive, no proper handling
}

// ❌ INCORRECT: Return 200 on errors
return res.status(200).json({ success: false });  // Should be 4xx or 5xx
```

