5. API Development Rules

5.1 API Route Structure

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT: Proper API route structure
// pages/api/video/generate.ts

import type { NextApiRequest, NextApiResponse } from 'next';
import config from '@/lib/config';
import { logger } from '@/lib/utils/logger';
import { successResponse, errorResponse, AppError } from '@/lib/utils/api-handler';
import { validateString, validateRequired } from '@/lib/utils/validation';
import { generateVideoWithFal } from '@/lib/services/fal';

export default async function handler(req: NextApiRequest, res: NextApiResponse) {
  // 1. Method check
  if (req.method !== 'POST') {
    return errorResponse(new AppError(405, 'Method not allowed'));
  }

  try {
    // 2. Input validation
    validateRequired(req.body.imageUrl, 'imageUrl');
    validateString(req.body.prompt, 'prompt', 500);

    // 3. Log the request
    logger.info('Video generation requested', {
      promptLength: req.body.prompt.length,
      hasImage: !!req.body.imageUrl,
    });

    // 4. Call service
    const result = await generateVideoWithFal({
      imageUrl: req.body.imageUrl,
      prompt: req.body.prompt,
    });

    // 5. Log success
    logger.info('Video generation completed', {
      videoUrl: result.videoUrl,
    });

    // 6. Return success
    return successResponse(result);

  } catch (error) {
    // 7. Log error
    logger.error('Video generation failed', {
      error: error instanceof Error ? error.message : 'Unknown error',
    });

    // 8. Return error (will be 4xx or 5xx)
    return errorResponse(error);
  }
}
```

5.2 API Rules

```yaml
API Development Rules:
  - ✅ Always validate inputs first
  - ✅ Always use structured logging
  - ✅ Always return proper HTTP status codes
  - ✅ Always use try-catch in handlers
  - ✅ Use service layer, never call external APIs directly
  - ✅ Rate limit all public endpoints
  - ✅ Never expose internal errors to users in production
  - ❌ Never return 200 for errors
  - ❌ Never use NEXT_PUBLIC_ variables in API routes
  - ❌ Never hardcode API keys
  - ❌ Never trust user input without validation
  - ❌ Never expose stack traces in production
```

5.3 Status Code Guide

Code When to Use
200 Successful GET, PUT, PATCH
201 Successful POST (resource created)
204 Successful DELETE
400 Bad request - invalid input
401 Unauthorized - no valid token
403 Forbidden - no permission
404 Resource not found
429 Too many requests - rate limited
500 Internal server error
502 Bad gateway - external API failed
503 Service unavailable - maintenance

