8. Code Review Checklist

8.1 Reviewer Must Check

```markdown
## Security Review
- [ ] No hardcoded API keys, tokens, or passwords
- [ ] No NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix on server-side environment variables
- [ ] API routes have proper input validation
- [ ] CORS is properly restricted (not wildcard *)
- [ ] Error responses don't leak internal details
- [ ] Rate limiting is implemented on new endpoints
- [ ] Authentication/authorization checks are in place

## Code Quality Review
- [ ] Code follows project naming conventions
- [ ] Functions are small and do one thing (< 50 lines)
- [ ] No duplicate code (DRY principle)
- [ ] Complex logic has explanatory comments
- [ ] Imports are organized (absolute > relative)
- [ ] No console.log in production code (use logger)

## Reliability Review
- [ ] All API calls have proper error handling
- [ ] External service calls have timeout and retry logic
- [ ] Loading and error states are handled in UI
- [ ] Edge cases are considered (null, empty, error)
- [ ] Fallback behavior is defined for failures

## Testing Review
- [ ] Unit tests cover the new/modified code
- [ ] Tests cover both success and failure paths
- [ ] Mock data is realistic and not exposing secrets
- [ ] Test descriptions clearly state what is being tested

## Performance Review
- [ ] No unnecessary re-renders in React components
- [ ] Images are optimized
- [ ] API calls are cached where appropriate
- [ ] Bundle size is not significantly increased

## Documentation Review
- [ ] README updated if new features added
- [ ] API changes are documented
- [ ] Environment variables are documented in .env.example
- [ ] Complex logic has inline comments
```

8.2 Automated Checks (CI/CD)

```yaml
# .github/workflows/ci.yml
name: CI Checks

on:
  pull_request:
    branches: [main, develop]
  push:
    branches: [main, develop]

jobs:
  security-scan:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v3
      - name: Check for exposed secrets
        run: |
          # Scan for hardcoded API keys
          ! grep -rE "sk-[a-zA-Z0-9]{20,}" --include="*.ts" --include="*.js" .
          ! grep -rE "NEXT_PUBLIC_(FAL|GROQ|GEMINI|SUPABASE_SERVICE)_" --include="*.ts" --include="*.js" .
      - name: Check .env files not committed
        run: |
          ! find . -name ".env" -o -name ".env.local" -o -name ".env.production" | grep .

  lint:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v3
      - uses: actions/setup-node@v3
      - run: npm ci
      - run: npm run lint

  type-check:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v3
      - uses: actions/setup-node@v3
      - run: npm ci
      - run: npm run type-check

  test:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v3
      - uses: actions/setup-node@v3
      - run: npm ci
      - run: npm test -- --coverage
      - name: Check coverage thresholds
        run: |
          # Ensure coverage meets minimum thresholds
          npx jest --coverage --coverageThreshold='{"global":{"lines":80,"branches":70,"functions":85,"statements":80}}'
```

